Job Summary:

An exciting opportunity with a Global organization as a Backend Software Engineer to support the critical development of new and existing infrastructure.

Mandatory Skill-set:
• Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Information Technology or related fields
• At least 4 years experience including hands-on designing and implementing software solutions;
• Experience in any of these programming languages Go, Java, Kotlin or Groovy;
• Experience in troubleshooting Kubernetes clusters and deployment;
• Technically competent with good analytical skills;
• Strong communication and interpersonal skills required for liaising with end-users of all levels as well as vendors;
• Team player with positive service mindset.

Desired Skill-set:
• Azure or AWS experience.
Responsibilities:
• Working individually and as a team, you should adopt an Agile approach;
• Dive deep into architecting a reliable and scalable clusters of services;
• Hands-on development and scripting;
•... Build efficient and scalable backend system on AWS, Azure and Kubernetes with Spring Boot, Docket or Terraform
• Write testable codes in Kotlin or Go that communicate with upstream services;
• Maintain and monitor and resolve performance and scalability issues.;
• Work closely with different teams to deliver projects.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to [Confidential Information] at the earliest.
When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).
Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.
